## Notion Page Structure

Each function page in Notion will have:

### Properties
- **Name** (Title): Function name
- **Module** (Text): Python module path
- **Category** (Select): Music Workflow, Shared Core, Services, Scripts, Sync Framework
- **Tags** (Text): async, private, notion, spotify, eagle, etc.
- **Signature** (Text): Full function signature with types
- **Is Async** (Checkbox): Whether function is async
- **Is Private** (Checkbox): Whether function starts with `_`
- **Num Args** (Number): Number of arguments
- **File Path** (Text): Relative file path
- **Line Start/End** (Number): Line numbers in source file
- **Status** (Select): Active

### Page Body
1. **Documentation** section with docstring
2. **Decorators** section (if any) in code block
3. **Source Code** section with complete function code in Python code block
4. **Metadata** section with file location and generation info
